node.text:
This year's #Sandhurst Tom Surdyke Leadership Award winner goes to Cadet Ethan Erickson with The College of Saint Benedict Saint John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion.

The award is named in memory of Cadet Thomas Surdyke who died from injuries sustained while saving the life of a drowning stranger. Surdyke was a member of the Company B4 @b4_buffaloes Sandhurst team his Plebe year.

After a long grueling process, five teams were named the top teams of the Sandhurst Military Skills Competition.  During Sandhurst, 44 teams representing four U.S. service academies and 16 ROTC programs compete against one another in a variety of military related contests.

Congratulations to USMA Black who won the overall competition. The top teams are: 

1. USMA Black @usma_sandhurst 
2. USMA Gold
3. Company F1 @f1.firehouse 
4. University of North Georgia @ungcadets 
5. The College of St. Benedict St. John's University @fightingsaintsbattalion

node.text:
Meet West Point's First Captain!

Cadet Holland Pratt of Liberty Lake, Wash., has been selected First Captain of the U.S. Military Academy’s Corps of Cadets for the 2021-2022 academic year, achieving the highest position in the cadet chain of command. 

As First Captain, she is responsible for the overall performance of approximately 4,400-member Corps of Cadets. Her duties also include implementing a class agenda and acting as a liaison between the Corps and the administration. 

Most recently, Pratt, a military history major and Arabic minor, led approximately 1,200 cadets as the Regimental Commander of Cadet Field Training. She was instrumental in preparing cadets to assume duties as non-commissioned officers in the Corps of Cadets, instilling the warrior ethos, and inspiring cadets to professional excellence through physically and mentally demanding training.

“The motto I live by and shared with new cadets this past summer during training is “Eager to Serve, Willing to Lead. This phrase means that your number one priority is always service to others, your leadership position is a tool to accomplish that service and is never the end state,” Pratt said. “Being named First Captain means for me an opportunity to serve others to the best of my ability and pay tribute to the legacy of those mentors and friends who have helped me throughout my time at the academy.”
 
Pratt’s cadetship includes a variety of accomplishments and activities such as receiving the Phi Kappa Phi Peter Zhu Scholastic Achievement Award for exceptional academic research and performance, the Dean’s Pentathlete Award for five semesters for earning an “A” in every graded academic, military, and physical event in one semester, Superintendent’s Award for Excellence for being in the top five percent of the class academically, militarily, and physically, co-captain of the Women’s Handball Team, mentor for the Elevation Initiative Leadership Club, and earning the Recondo, Norwegian Foot March, and Air Assault badges.

Congratulations Cadet Pratt! 

For more information, visit West Point PAO Press Releases #GoArmy #USMA2022 #WestPoint #Leadership #USMA #FirstCaptain #usarmy

#Crucible Complete.

Cadet Leader Development Training for rising seniors (Firsties) and juniors (Cows) culminated in a 10-day Field Training Exercise, naming the last day the Crucible and dedicating the task force to C.J. Morgan, Class of 2020.

During the Crucible, cadets completed a five km ruck march while carrying mock casualty, full water containers, and ammunition. They were responsible for reaching nine checkpoints while experiencing smoke bombs, direct, and indirect fire.

Morale skyrocketed as the day ended in a highly charged platoon on platoon combatives tournament . This day marked the end of the ten-day FTX and ultimately the completion of #CLDT. Congratulations! #USMA2022 #USMA2023 #WestPoint #GoArmy

📸: Cadet Marco Copat, Class of 2022

node.text: The U.S. Army Chaplain Corps is one of the oldest and smallest branches of the Army. The Chaplain Corps dates back to July 29, 1775, when the Continental Congress authorized one chaplain for each regiment of the Continental Army. The Chaplain Corps consists of ordained clergy of multiple faiths who are commissioned Army officers serving as military chaplains as well as enlisted Soldiers who serve as assistants. Their purpose is to offer religious church services, counseling and moral support to the armed forces, whether in peacetime or at war.

Since 1992, America honors Buffalo Soldiers on July 28 to commemorate the first Army regiments comprised of African American Soldiers. 

The U.S. Military Academy salutes Buffalo Soldiers who served their country with pride and distinction at West Point. 

In September, the Buffalo Soldier Association of West Point will unveil a new monument at the U.S. Military Academy to be dedicated to the legacy of these elite horsemen.
